                                                      // So, (abs_n + abs_m) % 2 == (k - d) % 2.
                                                      //
                                                      // We want to maximize `d`.
                                                      // The maximum possible `d` is `k`.
                                                      // The minimum number of moves to reach (abs_n, abs_m) is `abs_n`.
                                                      // In these `abs_n` moves, we use `abs_m` diagonal moves and `abs_n - abs_m` axial moves.
                                                      // So, `d_min_path = abs_m`, `a_min_path = abs_n - abs_m`.
                                                      //
                                                      // The remaining `k - abs_n` moves must be "wasted" moves.
                                                      // Each wasted move must be paired with another move to return to the same spot,
